text: Justine Wong-Orantes (born October 6, 1995) is an American volleyball player. She played indoor and beach volleyball for University of Nebraska. She played for the United States national team, in 2017, she won the Pan American gold medal, and the bronze medal at the 2017 FIVB Volleyball World Grand Prix. == References == == See also == Category:Living people Category:1995 births Category:American women's volleyball players Category:Nebraska Cornhuskers women's beach volleyball players Category:Nebraska Cornhuskers women's volleyball players Category:Liberos
